0Ukraine%20began%20in%20February%202022%2C%20resulting%20in%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20deaths%20on%20both%20sides.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmid%20the%20raging%20military%20conflict%2C%20PM%20Modi%20has%20spoken%20to%20Putin%20as%20well%20as%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPM%20Modi%20also%20met%20Ukraine%20President%20Zelenskyy%20in%20Japan%20during%20the%20G7%20summit%20in%20May%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meeting%2C%20PM%20Modi%20assured%20that%20he%20would%20do%20whatever%20was%20possible%20to%20help%20resolve%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIndia%20and%20I%20will%20do%20whatever%20we%20can%20to%20resolve%20the%20conflict%2C%26quot%3B%20PM%20Modi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20Delhi%20has%20sought%20a%20diplomatic%20solution%20to%20the%20conflict%2C%20with%20PM%20Modi%20telling%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20in%20September%20that%20%26quot%3Bnow%20is%20not%20an%20era%20of%20war.%26quot%3B%20The%20remark%20drew%20praise%20from%20world%20leaders%20as%20well%20as%20the%20global%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Modi%20advised%20President%20Putin%20to%20ensure%20a%20%26quot%3Bcessation%20of%20violence%2C%26quot%3B%20stressing%20the%20need%20for%20both%20sides%20to%20return%20to%20the%20talks%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20telephonic%20conversation%20with%20Putin%2C%20PM%20Modi%20underlined%20that%20Delhi%20for%20now%20will%20stick%20to%20a%20path%20of%20strategic%20ambivalence%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20pragmatic%20choice%2C%20one%20that%20reflects%20the%20complexities%20of%20a%20realist%20world%20and%20Delhi's%20own%20positions%20on%20territorial%20integrity%20and%20sovereignty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703957520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%